do not go gentle ( welsh : oed yr addewid ) is a 2002 british film directed by emlyn williams . it was the united kingdom 's submission to the 74th academy awards for the academy award for best foreign language film , but was not accepted as a nominee . the film was produced by alun ffred jones and stars stewart jones , gwenno hodgkins , arwel gruffydd , marged esli , caroline berry and romolo bruni . the welsh title translates literally as " age pledge " . the english title is a reference to the dylan thomas poem " do not go gentle into that good night " .